    <text id="F3525T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>Several ministers of the German Reformed Church recommend John Ault as an Army
                    chaplain.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
               

                

                <p>The undersigned ministers belonging to the German Reformed Church, resident in
                    Franklin County Penna, and personally acquainted with Rev. John Ault, of Loudon
                    in the same county, do certify that he is a regularly ordained minister of the
                    German Reformed Church, and do testify to his good and regular standing as such
                    minister, and cheerfully and earnestly recommend him for appointment as an Army
                    Chaplain.</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute/>
                    <signed>Bernard C. Wolf pr<del rend="none" hand="h1"/> of <del rend="none" hand="h1"/><lb/> Minister of
                        Ger. Ref. Church<lb/><lb/> Isaac G. Brown<lb/> Mercersburg Pa.<lb/><lb/>
                        Saul R. Fisher, State Clerk<lb/> of S<del rend="none" hand="h1"/>d of Ger. Ref.
                        Church.<lb/><lb/> B. Bausman<lb/> Chambersburg, Pa.<lb/><lb/> W. R. H.
                        Deatrick<lb/> Pastor Grindstone Hill<lb/><lb/> Samuel Philips<lb/> Past. of
                        Carlisle Charge</signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
